Check possible batch effects

# Adonis2 test with complete counts

distance_matrix <- dist(t(countsTMM))

adonis2(distance_matrix ~ Group + Subgroup + Sample_Type + Extraction_protocol, data = pheno_data)
## Permutation test for adonis under reduced model
## Terms added sequentially (first to last)
## Permutation: free
## Number of permutations: 999
## 
## adonis2(formula = distance_matrix ~ Group + Subgroup + Sample_Type + Extraction_protocol, data = pheno_data)
##                     Df SumOfSqs      R2       F Pr(>F)    
## Group                1   877104 0.23829 21.2380  0.001 ***
## Subgroup             4   472253 0.12830  2.8588  0.001 ***
## Sample_Type          1    91687 0.02491  2.2201  0.017 *  
## Extraction_protocol  1    92297 0.02507  2.2349  0.018 *  
## Residual            52  2147535 0.58343                   
## Total               59  3680876 1.00000                   
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
# Batch effect correction

countsF_bash_ST <- ComBat_seq(counts=countsF, batch=pheno_data$Sample_Type)
## Found 2 batches
## Using null model in ComBat-seq.
## Adjusting for 0 covariate(s) or covariate level(s)
## Estimating dispersions
## Fitting the GLM model
## Shrinkage off - using GLM estimates for parameters
## Adjusting the data
countsF_bash_ST_ET <- ComBat_seq(counts=countsF_bash_ST, batch=pheno_data$Extraction_protocol)
## Found 2 batches
## Using null model in ComBat-seq.
## Adjusting for 0 covariate(s) or covariate level(s)
## Estimating dispersions
## Fitting the GLM model
## Shrinkage off - using GLM estimates for parameters
## Adjusting the data
d <- DGEList(counts = countsF_bash_ST_ET)
Norm.Factor <- calcNormFactors(d, method = "TMM")
countsTMM_corrected <- cpm(Norm.Factor, log = T)

x<-countsTMM_corrected

sample_conditions_G <- pheno_data$Group
names(sample_conditions_G) <- pheno_data$Sample

clust.cor.ward <- hclust(dist(t(x)),method="ward.D2")
plot(clust.cor.ward, main="hierarchical clustering labeled by group", hang=-1,cex=0.5)
labels_G <- sample_conditions_G[clust.cor.ward$order]
axis(side = 1, at = 1:length(labels_G), labels = labels_G, las = 2, cex.axis = 0.5)

# DEA AML vs. Ctr

dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = countsF,
                              colData = pheno_data,
                              design = ~ Group)
dds <- DESeq(dds)

res1 <- results(dds, contrast=c("Group","AML","Ctr"))
res1DF <- as.data.frame(res1)
res1DFS <- res1DF[order(res1DF$pvalue),]

top_genes_Ctr_AML <- res1DFS[res1DFS$padj<0.01 & abs(res1DFS$log2FoldChange) > 1,]
top_Ctr_AML <- rownames(top_genes_Ctr_AML)[1:500]

data.clus <- countsTMM[rownames(top_genes_Ctr_AML)[1:500],]

Subgroup profiles generation

# Generate profiles

selected_genes <- unique(c(top_Ctr_AML, all_top_genes))

NUP98_patients <- subset(pheno_data_AML, pheno_data_AML$Subgroup=="NUP98r")
KMT2A_patients <- subset(pheno_data_AML, pheno_data_AML$Subgroup=="KMT2Ar")
CBF_patients <- subset(pheno_data_AML, pheno_data_AML$Subgroup=="CBF")
APL_patients <- subset(pheno_data_AML, pheno_data_AML$Subgroup=="APL")
OTHER_patients <- subset(pheno_data_AML, pheno_data_AML$Subgroup=="OTHER")

Counts_NUP98 <- countsTMM[rownames(countsTMM) %in% selected_genes,NUP98_patients$Sample]
Counts_KMT2A <- countsTMM[rownames(countsTMM) %in% selected_genes,KMT2A_patients$Sample]
Counts_CBF <- countsTMM[rownames(countsTMM) %in% selected_genes,CBF_patients$Sample]
Counts_APL <- countsTMM[rownames(countsTMM) %in% selected_genes,APL_patients$Sample]
Counts_OTHER <- countsTMM[rownames(countsTMM) %in% selected_genes,OTHER_patients$Sample]


NUP98r_profile <- rowMeans(Counts_NUP98)
KMT2Ar_profile <- rowMeans(Counts_KMT2A)
CBF_profile <- rowMeans(Counts_CBF)
APL_profile <- rowMeans(Counts_APL)
OTHER_profile <- rowMeans(Counts_OTHER)


AML_profiles_matrix <- cbind(NUP98r_profile, KMT2Ar_profile, CBF_profile, APL_profile, OTHER_profile)

Subtypes <- c("NUP98r", "KMT2Ar", "CBF", "APL", "OTHERS")
Subtypes.df <- data.frame(Subtypes = Subtypes)
rownames(Subtypes.df) <- colnames(AML_profiles_matrix)
pheatmap::pheatmap(AML_profiles_matrix, scale = "row", show_rownames = FALSE, annotation_col = Subtypes.df, fontsize = 7,  angle_col = 90)

# Correlation Samples vs. Samples

pheno_AML_Ordered <- pheno_data_AML[order(pheno_data_AML$Subgroup),]

annot_subgroup <- data.frame(Subgroup = pheno_AML_Ordered$Subgroup)
rownames(annot_subgroup) <- pheno_AML_Ordered$Sample
pheatmap::pheatmap(cor, cluster_cols = F, cluster_rows = F, display_numbers = T, annotation_row = annot_subgroup, annotation_col = annot_subgroup, fontsize_number = 2.5, number_color = "Black", color = colorRampPalette(brewer.pal(8, "Greens"))(5), annotation_colors = list(Subgroup = c(APL = "#ff9289", CBF = "#ff8aff", KMT2Ar = "#00db98", NUP98r = "#00cbff", OTHER = "#bec100")), angle_col = "90")
